ieee8021paeMIB.name: ieee8021paeMIB
ieee8021paeMIB.description: The Port Access Entity module for managing IEEE 802.1X.

PaeControlledDirections.name: PaeControlledDirections
PaeControlledDirections.description: The control mode values for the Authenticator PAE.

PaeControlledPortStatus.name: PaeControlledPortStatus
PaeControlledPortStatus.description: The status values of the Authenticator PAE controlled Port.

PaeControlledPortControl.name: PaeControlledPortControl
PaeControlledPortControl.description: The control values of the Authenticator PAE controlled Port.

dot1xPaeSystemAuthControl.name: dot1xPaeSystemAuthControl
dot1xPaeSystemAuthControl.description: The administrative enable/disable state for Port Access Control in a System.

dot1xPaePortTable.name: dot1xPaePortTable
dot1xPaePortTable.description: A table of system level information for each port supported by the Port Access Entity. An entry appears in this table for each port of this system.

dot1xPaePortEntry.name: dot1xPaePortEntry
dot1xPaePortEntry.description: The Port number, protocol version, and initialization control for a Port.

dot1xPaePortNumber.name: dot1xPaePortNumber
dot1xPaePortNumber.description: The Port number associated with this Port.

dot1xPaePortProtocolVersion.name: dot1xPaePortProtocolVersion
dot1xPaePortProtocolVersion.description: The protocol version associated with this Port.

dot1xPaePortCapabilities.name: dot1xPaePortCapabilities
dot1xPaePortCapabilities.description: Indicates the PAE functionality that this Port supports and that may be managed through this MIB.

dot1xPaePortInitialize.name: dot1xPaePortInitialize
dot1xPaePortInitialize.description: The initialization control for this Port. Setting this attribute TRUE causes the Port to be initialized. The attribute value reverts to FALSE once initialization has completed.

dot1xPaePortReauthenticate.name: dot1xPaePortReauthenticate
dot1xPaePortReauthenticate.description: The reauthentication control for this port. Setting this attribute TRUE causes the Authenticator PAE state machine for the Port to reauthenticate the Supplicant. Setting this attribute FALSE has no effect. This attribute always returns FALSE when it is read.

dot1xAuthConfigTable.name: dot1xAuthConfigTable
dot1xAuthConfigTable.description: A table that contains the configuration objects for the Authenticator PAE associated with each port. An entry appears in this table for each port that may authenticate access to itself.

dot1xAuthConfigEntry.name: dot1xAuthConfigEntry
dot1xAuthConfigEntry.description: The configuration information for an Authenticator PAE.

dot1xAuthPaeState.name: dot1xAuthPaeState
dot1xAuthPaeState.description: The current value of the Authenticator PAE state machine.

dot1xAuthBackendAuthState.name: dot1xAuthBackendAuthState
dot1xAuthBackendAuthState.description: The current state of the Backend Authentication state machine.

dot1xAuthAdminControlledDirections.name: dot1xAuthAdminControlledDirections
dot1xAuthAdminControlledDirections.description: The current value of the administrative controlled directions parameter for the Port.

dot1xAuthOperControlledDirections.name: dot1xAuthOperControlledDirections
dot1xAuthOperControlledDirections.description: The current value of the operational controlled directions parameter for the Port.

dot1xAuthAuthControlledPortStatus.name: dot1xAuthAuthControlledPortStatus
dot1xAuthAuthControlledPortStatus.description: The current value of the controlled Port status parameter for the Port.

dot1xAuthAuthControlledPortControl.name: dot1xAuthAuthControlledPortControl
dot1xAuthAuthControlledPortControl.description: The current value of the controlled Port control parameter for the Port.

dot1xAuthQuietPeriod.name: dot1xAuthQuietPeriod
dot1xAuthQuietPeriod.description: The value, in seconds, of the quietPeriod constant currently in use by the Authenticator PAE state machine.

dot1xAuthTxPeriod.name: dot1xAuthTxPeriod
dot1xAuthTxPeriod.description: The value, in seconds, of the txPeriod constant currently in use by the Authenticator PAE state machine.

dot1xAuthSuppTimeout.name: dot1xAuthSuppTimeout
dot1xAuthSuppTimeout.description: The value, in seconds, of the suppTimeout constant currently in use by the Backend Authentication state machine.

dot1xAuthServerTimeout.name: dot1xAuthServerTimeout
dot1xAuthServerTimeout.description: The value, in seconds, of the serverTimeout constant currently in use by the Backend Authentication state machine.

dot1xAuthMaxReq.name: dot1xAuthMaxReq
dot1xAuthMaxReq.description: The value of the maxReq constant currently in use by the Backend Authentication state machine.

dot1xAuthReAuthPeriod.name: dot1xAuthReAuthPeriod
dot1xAuthReAuthPeriod.description: The value, in seconds, of the reAuthPeriod constant currently in use by the Reauthentication Timer state machine.

dot1xAuthReAuthEnabled.name: dot1xAuthReAuthEnabled
dot1xAuthReAuthEnabled.description: The enable/disable control used by the Reauthentication Timer state machine (8.5.5.1).

dot1xAuthKeyTxEnabled.name: dot1xAuthKeyTxEnabled
dot1xAuthKeyTxEnabled.description: The value of the keyTransmissionEnabled constant currently in use by the Authenticator PAE state machine.

dot1xAuthStatsTable.description: A table that contains the statistics objects for the Aut henticator PAE associated with each Port. An entry appears in this table for each port that may authenticate access to itself.

dot1xAuthStatsEntry.name: dot1xAuthStatsEntry
dot1xAuthStatsEntry.description: The statistics information for an Authenticator PAE.

dot1xAuthEapolFramesRx.description: The number of valid EAPOL frames of any type that have been received by this Authenticator.

dot1xAuthEapolFramesTx.name: dot1xAuthEapolFramesTx
dot1xAuthEapolFramesTx.description: The number of EAPOL frames of any type that have been transmitted by this Authenticator.

dot1xAuthEapolStartFramesRx.name: dot1xAuthEapolStartFramesRx
dot1xAuthEapolStartFramesRx.description: The number of EAPOL Start frames that have been received by this Authenticator.

dot1xAuthEapolLogoffFramesRx.description: The number of EAPOL Logoff frames that have been received by this Authenticator.

dot1xAuthEapolRespIdFramesRx.name: dot1xAuthEapolRespIdFramesRx
dot1xAuthEapolRespIdFramesRx.description: The number of EAP Resp/Id frames that have been received by this Authenticator.

dot1xAuthEapolRespFramesRx.name: dot1xAuthEapolRespFramesRx
dot1xAuthEapolRespFramesRx.description: The number of valid EAP Response frames (other than Resp/Id frames) that have been received by this Authenticator.

dot1xAuthEapolReqIdFramesTx.name: dot1xAuthEapolReqIdFramesTx
dot1xAuthEapolReqIdFramesTx.description: The number of EAP Req/Id frames that have been transmitted by this Authenticator.

dot1xAuthEapolReqFramesTx.name: dot1xAuthEapolReqFramesTx
dot1xAuthEapolReqFramesTx.description: The number of EAP Request frames (other than Rq/Id frames) that have been transmitted by this Authenticator.

dot1xAuthInvalidEapolFramesRx.name: dot1xAuthInvalidEapolFramesRx
dot1xAuthInvalidEapolFramesRx.description: The number of EAPOL frames that have been received by this Authenticator in which the frame type is not recognized.

dot1xAuthEapLengthErrorFramesRx.name: dot1xAuthEapLengthErrorFramesRx
dot1xAuthEapLengthErrorFramesRx.description: The number of EAPOL frames that have been received by this Authenticator in which the Packet Body Length field is invalid.

dot1xAuthLastEapolFrameVersion.name: dot1xAuthLastEapolFrameVersion
dot1xAuthLastEapolFrameVersion.description: The protocol version number carried in the most recently received EAPOL frame.

dot1xAuthLastEapolFrameSource.name: dot1xAuthLastEapolFrameSource
dot1xAuthLastEapolFrameSource.description: The source MAC address carried in the most recently received EAPOL frame.

dot1xAuthDiagTable.name: dot1xAuthDiagTable
dot1xAuthDiagTable.description: A table that contains the diagnostics objects for the Authenticator PAE associated with each Port. An entry appears in this table for each port that may authenticate access to itself.

dot1xAuthDiagEntry.name: dot1xAuthDiagEntry
dot1xAuthDiagEntry.description: The diagnostics information for an Authenticator PAE.

dot1xAuthEntersConnecting.name: dot1xAuthEntersConnecting
dot1xAuthEntersConnecting.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions to the CONNECTING state from any other state.

dot1xAuthEapLogoffsWhileConnecting.name: dot1xAuthEapLogoffsWhileConnecting
dot1xAuthEapLogoffsWhileConnecting.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from CONNECTING to DISCONNECTED as a result of receiving an EAPOL-Logoff message.

dot1xAuthEntersAuthenticating.name: dot1xAuthEntersAuthenticating
dot1xAuthEntersAuthenticating.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from CONNECTING to AUTHENTICATING, as a result of an EAP-Response/Identity message being received from the Supplicant.

dot1xAuthAuthSuccessWhileAuthenticating.name: dot1xAuthAuthSuccessWhileAuthenticating
dot1xAuthAuthSuccessWhileAuthenticating.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATING to AUTHENTICATED, as a result of the Backend Authentication state machine indicating successful authentication of the Supplicant (authSuccess = TRUE).

dot1xAuthAuthTimeoutsWhileAuthenticating.name: dot1xAuthAuthTimeoutsWhileAuthenticating
dot1xAuthAuthTimeoutsWhileAuthenticating.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATING to ABORTING, as a result of the Backend Authentication state machine indicating authentication timeout (authTimeout = TRUE).

dot1xAuthAuthFailWhileAuthenticating.name: dot1xAuthAuthFailWhileAuthenticating
dot1xAuthAuthFailWhileAuthenticating.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATING to HELD, as a result of the Backend Authentication state machine indicating authentication failure (authFail = TRUE).

dot1xAuthAuthReauthsWhileAuthenticating.name: dot1xAuthAuthReauthsWhileAuthenticating
dot1xAuthAuthReauthsWhileAuthenticating.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATING to ABORTING, as a result of a reauthentication request (reAuthenticate = TRUE).

dot1xAuthAuthEapStartsWhileAuthenticatin.name: dot1xAuthAuthEapStartsWhileAuthenticating
dot1xAuthAuthEapStartsWhileAuthenticatin.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATING to ABORTING, as a result of an EAPOL-Start message being received from the Supplicant.

dot1xAuthAuthEapLogoffWhileAuthenticatin.name: dot1xAuthAuthEapLogoffWhileAuthenticating
dot1xAuthAuthEapLogoffWhileAuthenticatin.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATING to ABORTING, as a result of an EAPOL-Logoff message being received from the Supplicant.

dot1xAuthAuthReauthsWhileAuthenticated.name: dot1xAuthAuthReauthsWhileAuthenticated
dot1xAuthAuthReauthsWhileAuthenticated.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATED to CONNECTING, as a result of a reauthentication request (reAuthenticate = TRUE).

dot1xAuthAuthEapStartsWhileAuthenticated.name: dot1xAuthAuthEapStartsWhileAuthenticated
dot1xAuthAuthEapStartsWhileAuthenticated.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATED to CONNECTING, as a result of an EAPOL-Start message being received from the Supplicant.

dot1xAuthAuthEapLogoffWhileAuthenticated.name: dot1xAuthAuthEapLogoffWhileAuthenticated
dot1xAuthAuthEapLogoffWhileAuthenticated.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATED to DISCONNECTED, as a result of an EAPOL-Logoff message being received from the Supplicant.

dot1xAuthBackendResponses.name: dot1xAuthBackendResponses
dot1xAuthBackendResponses.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine sends an initial Access-Request packet to the Authentication server (i.e., executes sendRespToServer on entry to the RESPONSE state). Indicates that the Authenticator attempted communication with the Authentication Server.

dot1xAuthBackendAccessChallenges.name: dot1xAuthBackendAccessChallenges
dot1xAuthBackendAccessChallenges.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine receives an initial Access-Challenge packet from the Authentication server (i.e., aReq becomes TRUE, causing exit from the RESPONSE state). Indicates that the Authentication Server has communication with the Authenticator.

dot1xAuthBackendOtherRequestsToSupplican.name: dot1xAuthBackendOtherRequestsToSupplicant
dot1xAuthBackendOtherRequestsToSupplican.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine sends an EAP-Request packet (other than an Identity, Notification, Failure or Success message) to the Supplicant (i.e., executes txReq on entry to the REQUEST state). Indicates that the Authenticator chose an EAP-method.

dot1xAuthBackendNonNakResponsesFromSuppl.name: dot1xAuthBackendNonNakResponsesFromSupplicant
dot1xAuthBackendNonNakResponsesFromSuppl.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine receives a response from the Supplicant to an initial EAP-Request, and the response is something other than EAP-NAK (i.e., rxResp becomes TRUE, causing the state machine to transition from REQUEST to RESPONSE, and the response is not an EAP-NAK). Indicates that the Supplicant can respond to the Authenticator's chosen EAP-method.

dot1xAuthBackendAuthSuccesses.name: dot1xAuthBackendAuthSuccesses
dot1xAuthBackendAuthSuccesses.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine receives an EAP-Success message from the Authentication Server (i.e., aSuccess becomes TRUE, causing a transition from RESPONSE to SUCCESS). Indicates that the Supplicant has successfully authenticated to the Authentication Server.

dot1xAuthBackendAuthFails.name: dot1xAuthBackendAuthFails
dot1xAuthBackendAuthFails.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine receives an EAP-Failure message from the Authentication Server (i.e., aFail becomes TRUE, causing a transition from RESPONSE to FAIL). Indicates that the Supplicant has not authenticated to the Authentication Server.

dot1xAuthSessionStatsTable.name: dot1xAuthSessionStatsTable

dot1xAuthSessionStatsEntry.description: The session statistics information for an Authenticator PAE. This shows the current values being collected for each session that is still in progress, or the final values for the last valid session on each port where there is no session currently active.

dot1xAuthSessionOctetsRx.name: dot1xAuthSessionOctetsRx

dot1xAuthSessionOctetsTx.name: dot1xAuthSessionOctetsTx
dot1xAuthSessionOctetsTx.description: The number of octets transmitted in user data frames on this Port during the session.

dot1xAuthSessionFramesRx.name: dot1xAuthSessionFramesRx
dot1xAuthSessionFramesRx.description: The number of user data frames received on this Port during the session.

dot1xAuthSessionFramesTx.name: dot1xAuthSessionFramesTx
dot1xAuthSessionFramesTx.description: The number of user data frames transmitted on this Port during the session.

dot1xAuthSessionId.name: dot1xAuthSessionId
dot1xAuthSessionId.description: A unique identifier for the session, in the form of a printable ASCII string of at least three characters.

dot1xAuthSessionAuthenticMethod.name: dot1xAuthSessionAuthenticMethod
dot1xAuthSessionAuthenticMethod.description: The authentication method used to establish the session.

dot1xAuthSessionTime.name: dot1xAuthSessionTime
dot1xAuthSessionTime.description: The duration of the session in seconds.

dot1xAuthSessionTerminateCause.name: dot1xAuthSessionTerminateCause
dot1xAuthSessionTerminateCause.description: The reason for the session termination.

dot1xAuthSessionUserName.name: dot1xAuthSessionUserName
dot1xAuthSessionUserName.description: The User-Name representing the identity of the Supplicant PAE.
